    "b, We test this procedure using error model simulations from n = 8 to 18 with increased laser intensity noise to emulate the fidelity expected for the experimental n = 60 dataset.",
    "For t > 6.6 cycles and n > 15, we only train on bond dimensions below the level necessary for exact simulation to mimic constraints at large system sizes.",
    "We observe two behaviours: (1) the ensemble prediction is consistent with the ground truth, and (2) the fidelity seems to follow a non-exponential form.",
    "See the Supplementary Information for further crosschecks, as well as analytic evidence for the origin of the non-exponential decay due to non-Markovian noise.",
